# Padroes Cypress para Testes E2E

## Estrutura Base

```ts
describe("Login", () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    cy.visit("/login");
  });

  it("faz login com credenciais validas", () => {
    cy.get('[data-cy="email"]').type("admin@test.com");
    cy.get('[data-cy="password"]').type("password123");
    cy.contains("button", "Entrar").click();
    cy.url().should("include", "/dashboard");
    cy.contains("h1", "Dashboard").should("be.visible");
  });

  it("exibe erro com credenciais invalidas", () => {
    cy.get('[data-cy="email"]').type("wrong@test.com");
    cy.get('[data-cy="password"]').type("wrong");
    cy.contains("button", "Entrar").click();
    cy.get('[role="alert"]').should("contain", "Credenciais invalidas");
  });
});
```

## Seletores (Ordem de Preferencia)

```ts
cy.contains("button", "Salvar");        // texto + tag
cy.get('[role="heading"]');              // role ARIA
cy.get('[data-cy="submit-form"]');       // data-cy (preferido sobre id/class)
cy.get("#email");                        // id (evitar)
```

## Custom Commands

```ts
// cypress/support/commands.ts
Cypress.Commands.add("login", (email: string, password: string) => {
  cy.session([email, password], () => {
    cy.visit("/login");
    cy.get('[data-cy="email"]').type(email);
    cy.get('[data-cy="password"]').type(password);
    cy.contains("button", "Entrar").click();
    cy.url().should("include", "/dashboard");
  });
});

// Uso
cy.login("admin@test.com", "password123");
```

## Intercept (Mock de API)

```ts
cy.intercept("GET", "/api/users", { fixture: "users.json" }).as("getUsers");
cy.visit("/users");
cy.wait("@getUsers");
cy.get("table tbody tr").should("have.length", 3);

// Verificar request
cy.intercept("POST", "/api/users").as("createUser");
cy.contains("button", "Criar").click();
cy.wait("@createUser").its("request.body").should("deep.include", {
  name: "Joao",
});
```

## Fixtures e Aliases

```ts
// cypress/fixtures/users.json
[{ "id": 1, "name": "Joao" }, { "id": 2, "name": "Maria" }]

// Uso com alias
cy.fixture("users.json").as("usersData");
cy.get("@usersData").then((users) => {
  expect(users).to.have.length(2);
});
```

## Convencoes

- `data-cy` como atributo de teste (nunca classes CSS)
- `cy.session` para login reutilizavel entre testes
- `cy.intercept` para controlar respostas de API
- Nunca usar `cy.wait(ms)` (preferir `cy.wait("@alias")`)
- `should` para assercoes com retry automatico
- Fixtures em `cypress/fixtures/` para dados de teste
