# Cypress E2E Test Patterns

## Base Structure

```ts
describe("Login", () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    cy.visit("/login");
  });

  it("logs in with valid credentials", () => {
    cy.get('[data-cy="email"]').type("admin@test.com");
    cy.get('[data-cy="password"]').type("password123");
    cy.contains("button", "Sign in").click();
    cy.url().should("include", "/dashboard");
    cy.contains("h1", "Dashboard").should("be.visible");
  });

  it("shows error with invalid credentials", () => {
    cy.get('[data-cy="email"]').type("wrong@test.com");
    cy.get('[data-cy="password"]').type("wrong");
    cy.contains("button", "Sign in").click();
    cy.get('[role="alert"]').should("contain", "Invalid credentials");
  });
});
```

## Selectors (Priority Order)

```ts
cy.contains("button", "Save");          // text + tag
cy.get('[role="heading"]');              // ARIA role
cy.get('[data-cy="submit-form"]');       // data-cy (preferred over id/class)
cy.get("#email");                        // id (avoid)
```

## Custom Commands

```ts
// cypress/support/commands.ts
Cypress.Commands.add("login", (email: string, password: string) => {
  cy.session([email, password], () => {
    cy.visit("/login");
    cy.get('[data-cy="email"]').type(email);
    cy.get('[data-cy="password"]').type(password);
    cy.contains("button", "Sign in").click();
    cy.url().should("include", "/dashboard");
  });
});

// Usage
cy.login("admin@test.com", "password123");
```

## Intercept (API Mocking)

```ts
cy.intercept("GET", "/api/users", { fixture: "users.json" }).as("getUsers");
cy.visit("/users");
cy.wait("@getUsers");
cy.get("table tbody tr").should("have.length", 3);

// Verify request
cy.intercept("POST", "/api/users").as("createUser");
cy.contains("button", "Create").click();
cy.wait("@createUser").its("request.body").should("deep.include", {
  name: "John",
});
```

## Fixtures and Aliases

```ts
// cypress/fixtures/users.json
[{ "id": 1, "name": "John" }, { "id": 2, "name": "Jane" }]

// Usage with alias
cy.fixture("users.json").as("usersData");
cy.get("@usersData").then((users) => {
  expect(users).to.have.length(2);
});
```

## Conventions

- `data-cy` as test attribute (never CSS classes)
- `cy.session` for reusable login across tests
- `cy.intercept` to control API responses
- Never use `cy.wait(ms)` (prefer `cy.wait("@alias")`)
- `should` for assertions with automatic retry
- Fixtures in `cypress/fixtures/` for test data
